Source:  Journal of the Polynesian Society
Author:
Vol / Page:  55/153
Edition:
Quote:  <i>ma[a]kutu,</i> bewitch; spell, incantation, for purpose of bewitching: commonly regarded as magic, witchcraft, of which there were two varieties; black (evil) and white (good).
Notes:  Andersen Maori Words in English

